Explanation of examples:
------------------------

- example1:  Ca/Mg substitutions in a 2x2x2 supercell of rocksalt MgO. VASP input files created (FILER=11). The pre-generated VASP inputs are in n16.

- example2:  Al/Fe substitution in magnetite Fe3O4 (cubic unit cell of the spinel structure). The substitution occurs in both tetrahedral and octahedral sites, allowing the study of the distribution of substitutions over the two different sites. VASP input files created (FILER=11). The pre-generated VASP inputs are in n04.

- example3:  Fe/Sb disorder in a 2x2x2 supercell of rutile FeSbO4. Starting from a generic MO2 composition, M(IV) is replaced by equal parts of Fe(III) and Sb(V). VASP input files created (FILER=11). The pre-generated VASP inputs are in n08. See Grau-Crespo et al. Chemistry of Materials (2004): https://pubs.acs.org/doi/abs/10.1021/cm035271y.

- example4:  Al/Fe substitution in a 2x2x2 supercell of LaFeO3 perovskite, using GULP (FILER=1). Also contains examples of energy extrapolation using SPBE0 and SPBE1 (see folders inside n04) and of grand-canonical statistics (x0.25 folder).

- example5:  Averaging NMR spectra in the canonical or grand-canonical configurational space of the La2Zr2O7-La2Sn2O7 solid solution. CASTEP input files are generated (FILER=12). The DFT calculation files are excluded to save space; only the statistical analysis files (ENERGIES, PEAKS, SPECTRA, etc.) are included in the n00-n16 folders.

- example6:  Mg/Zn substitution in a 2x2x1 supercell of wurtzite ZnO (space group 186, P6_3mc). The 8 cation sites with 2 Mg substitutions (Mg_0.25Zn_0.75O) reduce to 3 inequivalent configurations under the hexagonal symmetry. Quantum ESPRESSO input files are generated (FILER=13). Includes top.qe and bottom.qe templates; replace Mg.upf, Zn.upf, O.upf with your pseudopotential files before running.
